hackathon-description-text: Hackital is a new undergraduate hackathon in the nation's capital planned by the George Washington Unisity students.

hackathon-judges.judge-role: Director, Student Entrepreneurship Programs / GW Innovation Office

hackathon-eligibility:
Please bring your ID with you.  
Teams of up to 4 people.
hackathon-rules:
Please adhere to the MLH code of conduct.
https://static.mlh.io/docs/mlh-code-of-conduct.pdf

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Use your tech skills for good and hack online harassment. Build a software solution that can help reduce the frequency and/or severity of online harassment. Win a HackHarassment Swag Bag.

Everything is part of the internet of things now - from your phone to your fitness band to your thermostat. Build a hack that utilizes private data being collected from your devices, and show how you can turn potential vulnerabilities into something constructive. Prize: Collector's Edition of Watch Dogs 2
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Watch Dogs® 2 Best Device Privacy Hack
Amazon Web Services - Best Use of AWS

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Use some internet sourced data. That's any API, Web crawling, RSS, etc..
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Best App using internet sourced data | Provided by Book Holders

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Longest stack name will win a Raspberry Pi or Arduino hardware
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Longest Stack Name | provided by Book Holders

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=419 7th St NW, Washington, DC 20004, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion:
Projects for Hackital will be judged on Technical Difficulty, Creativity & Innovation, and Practicality. 
Each team will have 2 minutes to demo their project in front of everyone.

hackathon-description-header: A New Hackathon in our Nation’s Capital.
